      <p>The landmark <strong>Q-SYMBIO trial</strong> (2014) enrolled 420 patients with severe heart failure across 17 centers in 9 countries. Patients receiving <strong>300mg CoQ10 daily</strong> for 2 years experienced a <strong>43% reduction in cardiovascular mortality</strong> and a 42% reduction in all-cause mortality compared to placebo. This was the first large-scale, randomized, double-blind trial to demonstrate that CoQ10 supplementation significantly improves survival outcomes in heart failure — a finding that prompted the European Society of Cardiology to acknowledge CoQ10 as a potential adjunctive therapy.</p>
